Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine light brown. Circular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 185, 16. Name Eukratidas. From same die as BM 1925,0119.112 and 430 and Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0919.05.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0375)
